description:
It's called Mortal Kombat (II).
Mortal Kombat II ‚Äì only in theaters and @imax October 24. #MortalKombatMovie #FilmedForIMAX 

From New Line Cinema comes the latest high-stakes installment in the blockbuster video game franchise in all its brutal glory, Mortal Kombat II.  This time, the fan favorite champions‚Äînow joined by Johnny Cage himself‚Äîare pitted against one another in the ultimate, no-holds barred, gory battle to defeat the dark rule of Shao Kahn that threatens the very existence of the Earthrealm and its defenders.

Karl Urban stars as Johnny Cage, alongside Adeline Rudolph, Jessica McNamee, Josh Lawson, Ludi Lin, Mehcad Brooks, Tati Gabrielle, Lewis Tan, Damon Herriman, with Chin Han, Tadanobu Asano as Lord Raiden, Joe Taslim as Bi-Han, and Hiroyuki Sanada as Hanzo Hasashi and Scorpion.

Director Simon McQuoid returns to helm the follow up to his explosive 2021 cinematic adventure, from a screenplay by Jeremy Slater, based on the videogame created by Ed Boon and John Tobias.  The film is produced by Todd Garner, James Wan, Toby Emmerich, E. Bennett Walsh and McQuoid, and executive produced by Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Slater and Lawrence Kasanoff.  

Joining McQuoid behind the camera are director of photography Stephen F. Windon, production designer Yohei Taneda, editor Stuart Levy and costume designer Cappi Ireland, with casting by Rich Delia and music by Benjamin Wallfisch.

New Line Cinema Presents an Atomic Monster/Broken Road Production, a Fireside Films Production, Mortal Kombat II.  The film will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, only in theaters and IMAX¬Æ across North America on October 24, 2025, and internationally beginning 22 October 2025.

name: Reuniting With My Family and Girlfriend After 2 Years
description:
MY BROTHER IS HOME!! üò≠‚úàÔ∏è Emotional Missionary Homecoming After 2 Years

After two years away, Brock is finally HOME!! He spent the last year and a half serving in Boston, Massachusetts, and this vlog captures the unforgettable moments leading up to his return. From packing his (very heavy) bags and saying goodbye to mission friends, to getting paired with a final companion‚Äîhis journey back was emotional and full of meaning.

Back at home, I was getting everything ready for his arrival‚Äîstocking the pantry (per Brock‚Äôs special request), grabbing some of his favorite foods, and prepping the house for a big surprise. We stayed up late making posters (yes, including a hilarious ‚Äúmarry me‚Äù one and some Fortnite-themed signs üòÇ) and decorated everything to make his homecoming extra special.

He landed in Salt Lake City, and the moment he walked through those airport doors‚Ä¶ we were all in tears. Our mom cried, and the biggest surprise of all‚Äîhis girlfriend was there to meet him even though he thought she‚Äôd still be out of town üëÄ

Once we got home, Brock saw his room for the first time, opened his welcome-back gift basket, and we wrapped up the perfect day with a Bees baseball game as a family. It was one of those days we‚Äôll never forget.

We had a bunch of interviews and hilarious moments throughout the entire trip, so be sure to stick around to the end of the video!

Thank you so much to all of the players for their time, we‚Äôre so excited to see how all of them continue to ball out in the second half. Also thank you so much to MLB for giving us credentialed access to talk to the games biggest stars on the biggest stage. Finally, thank you to you all for your continued support ‚ù§Ô∏è none of this is possible without you guys and we are so grateful to be able to go on these adventures because of you all.
